{
  "text": "CDSS was used to evaluate depressive symptoms. To distinguish patients with depression from those without depression, the value of 7 was used as a cut-off point. The same value was used by Addington et al to distinguish between depressive patients and patients without depression (40), by Bressan et al to distinguish between patients with major depression and patients with moderate or without depression (41), and Müller et al to distinguish between patients with moderate and severe depression and those with mild depression or without depression [CITATION_1] .",
